 +
3.  Click *Add Hardware*. The *Adding Virtual Hardware* dialog
appears. +
 +
http://www.gluster.org/community/documentation/index.php/File:Gluster-32-gvsa-kvm-configure3.jpg[image:/community/documentation/images/thumb/b/b7/Gluster-32-gvsa-kvm-configure3.jpg/500px-Gluster-32-gvsa-kvm-configure3.jpg[Gluster-32-gvsa-kvm-configure3.jpg]] +
 +
4.  Select *Storage* and click *Foward*. The Storage screen appears. +
 +
http://www.gluster.org/community/documentation/index.php/File:Gluster-32-gvsa-kvm-configure4.jpg[image:/community/documentation/images/thumb/c/c5/Gluster-32-gvsa-kvm-configure4.jpg/500px-Gluster-32-gvsa-kvm-configure4.jpg[Gluster-32-gvsa-kvm-configure4.jpg]] +
 +
5.  Specify the disk capacity, select Device type as *Virtio Disk*.
6.  Click *Forward*. The *Finish Adding Virtual Hardware* dialog
appears. +
 +
